From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on rabies in Mexico were abstracted from
GIDEON <http://www.cyinfo.com>:
Most cases are reported from Mexico, Oaxaca and Puebla States.
There were 426 cases of human rabies were reported during 1978 to 1984; and
632 during 1980 to 1988 (approximately 50% of cases for all of Latin America).
Year Human rabies Animal rabies
1980 40 10,825
1981 59 2,140
1982 45 2,303
1983 47 2,655
1984 63 3,850
1985 84 1,839
1986 85 6,250
1987 60 13,784
1988 72 13,048
1989 65 11,560
1990 69 13,128
1991 48 8,058
1992 35 2,006
1993 29 1,406
1994 25 * 1,982 (88.8% dogs)
1995 31 1,447 (95.9% dogs)
1996 22 2,387 (100% dogs)
1997 26 601 (preliminary)
1998 15
* 31 634 humans were given post-exposure prophylaxis in 1994.
